</form><html xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:math="java.lang.Math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:fo="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Format" xmlns:fn="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-functions" xmlns:xdt="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-datatypes" xmlns:caml="http://lc.ca.gov/legalservices/schemas/caml.1#" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head><title>AB2380:v98#DOCUMENT</title><meta name="dc:identifier" content="AB2380"/><meta name="dc:title" content="AB &#xA;              2380-&#xA;                AMENDED&#xA;              "/><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html;charset=utf-8"/></head><body><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Start</h2></span><div id="bill_all" align="justify"><div id="about"><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td align="center"><span style=" text-transform: uppercase; font-size: 1em">
                Amended
               IN </span><span style=" text-transform: uppercase; font-size: 1em">
                Senate
              </span> <span style="text-transform: uppercase">June 10, 2026</span><br/></td></tr></tbody><tbody><tr><td align="center"/></tr></tbody></table></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><font size="3" style="FONT-FAMILY: MinionPC, Arial Unicode MS">
                    CALIFORNIA LEGISLATURE—
                    2025–2026 REGULAR SESSION</font></div><br clear="all"/><span id="bill_house_num"><div style="float: left; width:50%; font-weight: bold; "><span style="text-transform: uppercase; text-align:left;width:50%;"><b>
                Assembly Bill
              </b></span></div><div style="float:right; width:50%; text-align:right;"><span style="text-transform: uppercase;"><b>No. 2380</b></span></div></span><hr/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td id="bill_authors" align="center"><span style="font-weight:bold;">Introduced by Assembly Member Papan<br/></span></td></tr><tr><td id="bill_intro_date" align="center" class="textcenter"><br/>February 19, 2026</td></tr></tbody></table></div><hr/><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;">An act to amend Sections 11734, 11923, 12034, 15204, and 15204.5 of the Food and Agricultural Code, relating to pest control.</span></div><br clear="all"/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">AB 2380, as amended, Papan.
                          Pest control: registration fees.</span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Existing law authorizes the board of supervisors of any county to establish reasonable fees for the registration of any person advertising, soliciting, or operating as a pest control business and limits the registration fee of certain pest control businesses to the amount necessary to cover the costs of registration, not to exceed $25.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This bill would raise the maximum<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> total</i></font> registration fee amount from $25 to<font color="#B30000"><strike> $75.</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>
			 $75 for a pest control business to register in its home county and to $50 to register in an additional county, as provided.</i></font></div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Existing law authorizes county boards of supervisors to set fees for registration to cover the cost of registering pest control aircraft pilots and pest control advisers, and limits those fees to no more than $10 per year for a pilot who registers in person in the county in which they intend to work and for an adviser who registers in person in the county listed in the adviser’s address on a specified license or the county of occupational choice, and no more than $5 per year for a pilot or adviser already registered in a county to register in an additional county, as provided.</div><font color="#B30000"><strike><p style="display:inline;"><s>This bill would repeal those annual registration fee limits of $10 and $5.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This bill would raise the maximum total registration fee amount for a pest control aircraft pilot and pest control adviser to register in their home county and in an additional county, as specified.</div></i></font><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Existing law requires certain licensed structural pest control operator qualifying managers and<font color="#B30000"><strike> structural pest control board</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> Structural Pest Control Board</i></font> registered companies to register with the county agricultural commissioner before operating a structural pest control business in the county. Existing law authorizes county boards of supervisors to require a registration fee not to exceed the actual cost of processing the registration or $10, whichever is less.</div><font color="#B30000"><strike><p style="display:inline;"><s>This bill would repeal that registration fee limit of $10.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This bill would raise the maximum total registration fee amount for a Structural Pest Control Board registered company to register in its home county and in an additional county, as specified.</div></i></font><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Existing law prohibits certain licensed structural pest controller licensees, as provided, from conducting fumigations in any county unless that person has also registered for the current calendar year with the county agricultural commissioner in that county, as provided. Existing law requires the county boards of supervisors to set that registration fee and for that fee not to exceed the cost of processing the registration or $25, whichever is less. Existing law authorizes structural pest control operators and field representatives to be added during the year and limits the fee for adding those operators and field representatives to the actual cost of processing the registration or $10, whichever is less.</div><font color="#B30000"><strike><p style="display:inline;"><s>This bill would repeal those annual registration fee limits of $25 and $10.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This bill would raise the maximum total registration fee amount for a Structural Pest Control Board registered company to register in its home county and in an additional county, as specified.</div></i></font></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="vote">
      Vote:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">MAJORITY</span>  </span><span id="appropriation">
      Appropriation:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span><span id="localprogram">
      Local Program:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><div id="bill"><div style=" text-transform: uppercase"><h2 style=" text-align: left;">The people of the State of California do enact as follows:</h2><br/></div><div id="s10.5238989079115459"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0" class="ActionLine"><h3 style="font-weight:bold; display:inline;">SECTION 1.</h3> Section 11734 of the Food and Agricultural Code is amended to read:</div><div><div id="id_2B65D2E0-5896-4F95-B8AC-FB3C3592C545"><div><p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><h6 style="display:inline;">11734.</h6> The board of supervisors of any county may establish reasonable fees for the registration required under Section 11732. Payment of the fee shall be due by the date designated by the commissioner. However, registration fees for pest control businesses licensed pursuant to Section 11704 shall be that amount necessary to cover the costs of registration, but shall not exceed seventy-five dollars ($75) per<font color="#B30000"><strike> year.</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> year in its home county and fifty dollars ($50) per year for each additional county.</i></font></div></p></div></div></div></div><div id="s20.5728441526883925"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0" class="ActionLine"><h3 style="font-weight:bold; display:inline;">SEC. 2.</h3> Section 11923 of the Food and Agricultural Code is amended to read:</div><div><div id="id_1181CC99-83AF-443E-9FAF-AA2BFE9395A8"><div><p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><h6 style="display:inline;">11923.</h6> <font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>(a) </i></font>County boards of supervisors may set fees for registration to cover the cost of registering pest control aircraft pilots pursuant to Section 11920.</div><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(b) For a pest control aircraft pilot who registers in their home county, the total amount of registration fees shall not exceed the following:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(1) Fifty-five dollars ($55) per year in calendar year 2027.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) Sixty-five dollars ($65) per year in calendar year
						2028.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(3) Seventy-five dollars ($75) per year in calendar year 2029 and later.</div></i></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(c) For a pest control aircraft pilot who is already registered pursuant to subdivision (b) and is registering in an additional county, the total amount of the registration fees for registering in the additional county shall not exceed the following:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(1) Ten dollars ($10) per year in calendar year 2027.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) Fifteen dollars ($15) per year in calendar year 2028.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(3) Twenty-five dollars ($25) per year in calendar year 2029 and later.</div></i></font></p></div></div></div></div><div id="s30.10115509179330795"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0" class="ActionLine"><h3 style="font-weight:bold; display:inline;">SEC. 3.</h3> Section 12034 of the Food and Agricultural Code is amended to read:</div><div><div id="id_D228C153-2DAF-4386-91E1-88530FC1EAB1"><div><p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><h6 style="display:inline;">12034.</h6> <font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>(a) </i></font>County boards of supervisors may set fees for registration to cover the cost of registering pest control advisers pursuant to Section 12031.</div><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(b) For a pest control adviser who registers in their home county, the total amount of registration fees shall not exceed the following:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(1) Fifty-five dollars ($55) per year in calendar year 2027.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) Sixty-five dollars ($65) per year in calendar year 2028.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(3) Seventy-five dollars ($75) per year in calendar year 2029 and later.</div></i></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(c) For a pest control adviser who is already registered pursuant to subdivision (b) and is registering in an additional county, the total amount of the registration fees for registering in the additional county shall not exceed the following:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(1) Ten dollars ($10) per year in calendar year 2027.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) Fifteen dollars ($15) per year in calendar year 2028.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(3) Twenty-five dollars ($25) per year in calendar year 2029 and later.</div></i></font></p></div></div></div></div><div id="s40.5171730319372767"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0" class="ActionLine"><h3 style="font-weight:bold; display:inline;">SEC. 4.</h3> Section 15204 of the Food and Agricultural Code is amended to read:</div><div><div id="id_6C6DE65E-933F-46A3-B3F5-7B96EE964DFA"><div><p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><h6 style="display:inline;">15204.</h6> (a) Each licensed Branch 2 and Branch 3 structural pest control operator qualifying manager, as defined in Section 8506.2 of the Business and Professions Code, and Structural Pest Control Board registered company, as defined in Section 8506.1 of the Business and Professions Code, shall register with the commissioner<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> of a county</i></font> before operating a structural pest control business in<font color="#B30000"><strike> the</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>
						that</i></font> county. The registration shall cover a calendar year. A fee may also be required at the time of registration. The fee shall be set by the county board of supervisors, except<font color="#B30000"><strike> that in no case shall</strike></font> the fee<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> shall not</i></font> exceed the actual cost of processing the
						registration. Payment of the fee shall be due by the date designated by the commissioner.</div><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(b) For a Structural Pest Control Board registered company that registers in its home county, the total amount of registration fees shall not exceed the following:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(1) Fifty-five dollars ($55) per year in calendar year 2027.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) Sixty-five dollars ($65) per year in calendar year 2028.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(3) Seventy-five dollars ($75) per year in calendar year 2029 and later.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(c) For a Structural Pest Control Board registered company that is already registered pursuant to subdivision (b) and is registering in an
						additional county, the total amount of the registration fees for registering in the additional county shall not exceed the following:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(1) Thirty dollars ($30) per year in calendar year 2027.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) Forty dollars ($40) per year in calendar year 2028.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(3) Fifty dollars ($50) per year in calendar year 2029 and later.</div></i></font><font color="#B30000"><strike><p style="display:inline;"><s>(b)</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></strike></font><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>(d)</i></font> Each registration shall be in a form prescribed by the director after consulting with the Structural Pest Control Board
						and commissioners and shall include the<font color="#B30000"><strike> structural pest control licensee’s</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>
						Structural Pest Control Board registered company’s</i></font> name and address, including all<font color="#B30000"><strike> satellite locations</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>
						branch offices</i></font> conducting business in the county, telephone numbers, responsible persons, and the type of pest control to be conducted.</div><font color="#B30000"><strike><p style="display:inline;"><s>(c)<span class="EnSpace"/>If ordered by the commissioner, other structural pest control licensees shall appear in person at the office of the commissioner to complete registration.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>(d)</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></strike></font><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>(e)</i></font> The commissioner may levy a civil penalty against any person who violates<font color="#B30000"><strike> the provisions of
						this section</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> this section,</i></font> in accordance with the procedures provided in Section 12999.5.</div></p></div></div></div></div><div id="s50.5913135474361533"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0" class="ActionLine"><h3 style="font-weight:bold; display:inline;">SEC. 5.</h3> Section 15204.5 of the Food and Agricultural Code is amended to read:</div><div><div id="id_1ABFCC0F-C977-432A-BA78-172C30342E1D"><div><p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><h6 style="display:inline;">15204.5.</h6> (a) <font color="#B30000"><strike>It is unlawful for any </strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>A </i></font>licensed Branch 1 Structural Pest<font color="#B30000"><strike> Controller</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> Control</i></font> licensee, including structural pest control operators, field representatives, applicators, and Structural Pest Control Board<font color="#B30000"><strike> (SPCB)</strike></font> registered companies, as defined in Section 8506.1 of the Business and Professions Code,<font color="#B30000"><strike> to</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>
						shall not</i></font> conduct fumigations in any county unless that person or company<font color="#B30000"><strike> has also</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> is</i></font> registered for the current calendar year with the commissioner in that county. The registration fee for the<font color="#B30000"><strike> SPCB</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> Structural Pest Control Board</i></font> registered<font color="#B30000"><strike> company</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> company,</i></font> including structural pest control<font color="#B30000"><strike> operators and</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>
						operators,</i></font> field<font color="#B30000"><strike> representatives</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>
						representatives,</i></font> and<font color="#B30000"><strike> applicators</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> applicators,</i></font> shall be set by the county Board of Supervisors, but shall not exceed the cost of processing the
						registration. Payment of the fee shall be due at registration or on a date set by the commissioner.<font color="#B30000"><strike> Structural pest control operators and field representatives may be added during the year, but the fee shall not exceed the actual cost of processing the registration.</strike></font></div><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(b) For a Structural Pest Control Board registered company that registers in its home county, the total amount of registration fees shall not exceed the following:</div></i></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(1) Fifty-five dollars ($55) per year in calendar year 2027.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) Sixty-five dollars ($65) per year in calendar year 2028.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(3) Seventy-five dollars ($75) per year in calendar year 2029 and later.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(c) For a Structural Pest Control Board registered company that is already registered pursuant to subdivision (b) and is registering in an additional county, the total amount of the registration fees for registering in the additional county shall not exceed the following:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(1) Thirty dollars ($30) per year in calendar year 2027.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) Forty dollars ($40) per year in calendar year 2028.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(3) Fifty dollars ($50) per year in calendar year 2029 and later.</div></i></font><font color="#B30000"><strike><p style="display:inline;"><s>(b)</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></strike></font><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>(d)</i></font> Each registration shall be in the form prescribed by the director after consulting with the<font color="#B30000"><strike> SPCB</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>
						Structural Pest Control Board</i></font> and the commissioners and shall include the name and address of the<font color="#B30000"><strike> SPCB</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>
						Structural Pest Control Board</i></font> registered company or structural pest control operator and all<font color="#B30000"><strike> satellite offices</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>
						branch locations</i></font> conducting business in the county, the name of the qualifying manager or the structural pest control operator and their license number, and a business telephone number. The registration form for field representatives and applicators shall include their name, license number, business address, and telephone number, and may be included with the business registration.</div><font color="#B30000"><strike><p style="display:inline;"><s>(c)<span class="EnSpace"/>Each licensed structural pest controller, including structural pest control operators, field representatives, applicators, or an SPCB registered company, that intends to conduct fumigation operations is required to appear in person at the office of the commissioner to complete the registration required by Section 15204.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>(d)</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></strike></font><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>(e)</i></font> Each<font color="#B30000"><strike> SPCB</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> Structural Pest Control Board</i></font> registered company or structural pest control operator that intends to conduct fumigation operations shall notify the agricultural commissioner at least 24 hours<font color="#B30000"><strike> prior to</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> before</i></font> commencing fumigation, or as approved on a case-by-case basis by the commissioner. This notice shall include all of the following:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(1) Name and address of the registered company or structural pest control operator.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) Address of the area or areas to be fumigated.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(3) The pesticide to be applied.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(4) The date of the intended application.</div><font color="#B30000"><strike><p style="display:inline;"><s>(e)</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></strike></font><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>(f)</i></font> The commissioner may levy a civil penalty against any person who violates this<font color="#B30000"><strike> section</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>
						section,</i></font> in accordance with the procedures provided in Section 12999.5.</div></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></body></html>
